This paper is about Bayesian inference for deep neural networks, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields of computer science. Based on the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on learning with neural networks and Bayesian model averaging. The next likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as Bayesian inference is a common technique in AI research. The paper also mentions image classification, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible sub-category. Additionally, the use of stochastic gradient descent (SGD) and variational inference suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the mention of well calibrated predictive uncertainty suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category, as uncertainty estimation is an important aspect of control systems.
